FAQs
What are the benefits of study in Canada?

Studying in Canada offers numerous benefits, including access to world-class education, a diverse and multicultural environment, and excellent career opportunities. Canada is known for its high quality of life and welcoming atmosphere.

How can I apply to a Canadian university?

You can apply to a Canadian university through university portals or centralized application systems like the Ontario Universities' Application Centre (OUAC). Start by researching universities and courses, then prepare the required documents, including academic transcripts, personal statements, letters of recommendation, and standardized test scores (if required). Ensure you meet all deadlines and follow the application guidelines provided by each university.

What scholarships are available for international students?

Canada offers various scholarships for international students, including merit-based and need-based scholarships. Many universities have their own scholarship programs, and there are also external scholarships offered by organizations such as Qadri-International and government agencies.

Can I work while studying in Canada?

Yes, international students on a study permit can work up to 20 hours per week during term time and full-time during holidays. Working while studying can provide valuable experience and help supplement your income, but it's important to balance work and academics.
